fields.physical_description:
[Westacre armchair (larger)] a dark stained wood single door wardrobe with turned wood details for  a dolls house, made by Elgin of Enfield, probably 1920s.
[Westacre armchair (small)] hand embroidered rug in multi coloured threads on a pale brown  background, backed with cream fabric. Made for a dolls' house, probably  1930-1960
[blanket box] turned wood (resembles mahogony) double bed for a dolls' house.The bed comes with a detachable mattress, valance, plain sheet, pillow and a floral quilt.
[embroidered picture] leather look arm chair
[vanity set] large rectangular rug in maroon, grey and yellow grid pattern
[lounge rug] large, curved cerimic vase in a dark, brown / grey colour, for a dolls' house
[lounge suite] vanity set comprising a metal-look hand mirror, brush and comb 
[telephone] pale pink floral three seater sofa with three matching plain pink cushions
[music stand] green metal telephone in two parts, body and reciever.

fields.history_note:
Part of the dolls' house accessories that furnish Peggy Lines' dolls house. There are a selection of furnishings included, many from the 1930s when Peggy would have played with the house and some later addiiosn from the next two generations of the family to play with the house.
companies represented include, Westacre Village, Dol-Toi and Lines Bros.
